BURGLARY SUSPECT TAKEN AT COUNTY COMPLEX 
San Diego police surrounded county office buildings at Ruffin Road and 
Clairemont Mesa Boulevard Sunday after an automatic burglar alarm sounded at 
7:47 a.m. 
After four hours, a police dog was sent in to the county complex and found an 
intruder, identified by police as Damon B. Miller. 
Miller suffered a minor wound from a dog bite. 
He was arrested and jailed on suspicion of 30 counts of commercial burglary. 
Police said no further details were available Sunday. 
